      "writtenOn": "2010-07-31T01:11:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When a device is turned off or a virtual voice call is ended, can you check if we get the CHUP before the SCO is closed ? Because we broadcast the state as Transferred here.",
      "revId": "4c5acac7c1e9f5af575bb2b3dcfce5ac147b9ce4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAA33///qg\u003d",
        "filename": "src/com/android/phone/BluetoothHandsfree.java",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 1027,
      "author": {
        "id": 1004035
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-08-02T08:29:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Whenever the call is ended, the AT+CHUP shall be received.\n\nWhen the headsets are powered off during a call, they do not send AT+CHUP. In this scenario, we shall only receive the SCO_CLOSED which will be treated as STATE_TRANSFERRED and subsequently after a ACL disconnect, we shall receive a terminateVirtualVoiceCall which shall trigger a STATE_DISCONNECTED intent.\n\nSo it is valid to send STATE_TRANSFERRED on SCO_CLOSED as we shall have no additional knowledge of the ACL state at this time.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA33///t4\u003d",
      "revId": "4c5acac7c1e9f5af575bb2b3dcfce5ac147b9ce4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAA33///ug\u003d",
        "filename": "src/com/android/phone/BluetoothHandsfree.java",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 1208,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000635
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-07-31T00:57:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think this is needed. The state is the same as the normal voice call. \nIf during a normal voice call - headsets powers down - we get SCO_CLOSED. The same thing will happen here to",
      "revId": "4c5acac7c1e9f5af575bb2b3dcfce5ac147b9ce4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
